[The East Lancashire Primary Care Trust serves a population of 414 684
residents from the 5 boroughs of Burnley, Hyndburn, Pendle, Ribbe
Valley and Rossendale. A map of the county of Lancashire in the north
of England can be accessed at:
http://www.manchester2002-uk.com/maps/lancs-map.html.

East Lancashire is an industrial area of the county with a degree of
social deprivation and unemployment with its attendant health problems
such drug abuse. The dramatic rise in case numbers over the past 2
years in East Lancashire, and Lancashire in general, is certainly
alarming. Although some forms of hepatitis C virus infection are
becoming treatable, the cost may not be sustainable without more
effective educational and social initiatives. - Mod.CP]
